block.translation:
“Though I gave to himwho deserved not the gift,

To the baser, the battle's prize;

Winters eightwast thou under the earth,

Milking the cows as a maid,

[Ay, and babes didst thou bear;

Unmanly thy soul must seem.]”

“They say that with spellsin Samsey once

Like witches with charms didst thou work;

And in witch's guiseamong men didst thou go;

Unmanly thy soul must seem.”
